  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A churning storm cloud forms for the duration, centered on a point within range and spreading to a radius of 300 feet. Each creature under the cloud when it appears must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take [[/r 5d6]] Thunder damage and is <em>deafened</em> for 5 minutes. On a successful save the creature takes half as much damage and is not <em>deafened</em>.</p><p>At the start of each of your turns, starting with the first round, the storm produces different effects, of your choice.</p><p><strong>Acid rain.</strong> Acidic rain falls from the cloud. Each creature and object under the cloud takes [[/r 5d6]] acid damage.</p><p><strong>Giant hailstones.</strong> Hailstones rain down from the cloud. Each creature under the cloud takes [[/r 5d6]] magicial bludgeoning damage.</p><p><strong>Lightning strikes.</strong> You call six bolts of lightning from the cloud to strike six different creatures or objects beneath it. Each target makes a Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 10d6]] lightning damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p><strong>Torrential sleet.</strong> Gusts and freezing rain assail the area under the cloud. Each creature there takes [[/r 3d6]] cold damage. Until the spell ends, the area is Difficult Terrain and Heavily Obscured, ranged attacks with weapons are impossible there, and strong wind blows through the area, automatically disperse fog, mists, and similar phenomena in the area, whether mundane or magical.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
